 {"event":{"class":"control","event":{"kind":"last_executor_diff_set","text":"diff --git a/SPEC.md b/SPEC.md\nindex c9648cd..6260203 100644\n--- a/SPEC.md\n+++ b/SPEC.md\n@@ -115,6 +115,44 @@ The system is a deterministic event-driven loop with explicit roles.\n - `ActionResult`: `{ complete: bool, output: string }`.\n - `RunConfig`: timeouts, tool availability, and patch scope policy.\n \n+### 1.5 Canonical Writer Infrastructure\n+\n+The orchestrator state machine is implemented as a **Canonical Writer** — a single deterministic gate for all serializable state mutations:\n+\n+```\n+W(s_t, e) → s_{t+1}\n+```\n+\n+Every state transition is represented as a typed `ControlEvent` variant, appended to the total-ordered log before the state transition executes. The gate is enforced by `CanonicalWriter::apply` in `src/canonical_writer.rs`.\n+\n+**Components:**\n+\n+| Component | Type | Role |\n+|-----------|------|------|\n+| `CanonicalWriter` | `src/canonical_writer.rs` | Single mutation gate: `apply(ControlEvent)` → logs then transitions |\n+| `SystemState` | `src/system_state.rs` | All serializable orchestrator state (phase, lanes, pending flags, diffs) |\n+| `RuntimeState` | `src/app.rs` | Non-serializable runtime-only state (tab handles, in-flight join sets) |\n+| `ControlEvent` | `src/events.rs` | Typed enum of all valid state transitions (23 variants) |\n+| `EffectEvent` | `src/events.rs` | Side-effect record (invariant violations, checkpoints) |\n+| `Tlog` | `src/tlog.rs` | Append-only NDJSON event log at `AgentStateDir/tlog.ndjson` |\n+\n+**Invariant gate:** Before emitting a `ControlEvent`, callers invoke `evaluate_invariant_gate` (`src/invariants.rs`). On violation the caller calls `writer.record_violation(...)` — which appends to the tlog without advancing state — and aborts the transition.\n+\n+**`RuntimeState` fields** (never serialized, never checkpointed):\n+- `submitted_turns: HashMap<(u32, u64), SubmittedExecutorTurn>` — active executor turns keyed by `(tab_id, turn_id)`\n+- `executor_submit_inflight: HashMap<usize, PendingSubmitState>` — in-flight submit tasks per lane\n+- `deferred_completions: HashMap<usize, VecDeque<DeferredExecutorCompletion>>` — completions queued while another is processing\n+\n+**`SystemState` key fields** (all serialized to checkpoint):\n+- `phase`, `phase_lane`, `scheduled_phase` — orchestration phase tracking\n+- `planner_pending`, `diagnostics_pending` — pending flags\n+- `lanes: HashMap<usize, LaneState>` — per-lane `{pending, in_progress_by, latest_verifier_result, plan_text}`\n+- `verifier_summary: Vec<String>` — per-lane verifier result summaries\n+- `lane_active_tab`, `tab_id_to_lane`, `lane_steps_used`, `lane_next_submit_at_ms`, `lane_submit_in_flight`, `lane_prompt_in_flight` — executor dispatch bookkeeping\n+- `submitted_turn_ids: HashMap<String, SubmittedTurnRecord>` — serializable record of in-flight executor turns\n+\n+**`apply_control_event`** (`src/system_state.rs`) is a pure function with no side effects. It is the only function permitted to construct `s_{t+1}` from `s_t`. All runtime code calls it exclusively through `CanonicalWriter::apply`.\n+\n ### 1.2 Role State (per agent)\n - `prompt_kind: PromptKind`\n - `step: u64` (monotonic, starts at 1 per role cycle)\n@@ -131,6 +169,7 @@ Canonical file paths are absolute under `Workspace` (see `src/constants.rs:3-11`\n - `LanePlan`: `PLANS/<instance>/executor-<id>.json` (preferred) or legacy `PLANS/executor-<id>.md` (see `src/tools.rs:49-63`)\n - `Violations`: `VIOLATIONS.json`\n - `Diagnostics`: runtime-configured instance-scoped path `PLANS/<instance>/diagnostics-<instance>.json`; legacy `DIAGNOSTICS.json` is still accepted for migration/read compatibility\n+- `Tlog`: `AgentStateDir/tlog.ndjson` — total-ordered NDJSON event log written by `CanonicalWriter`; one JSON record per line with fields `seq`, `ts_ms`, `event`. Authoritative replay source for all state transitions.\n \n ### 1.4 Workspace Resolution Rule\n Every `path` field in every action is resolved as follows:\n@@ -348,7 +387,7 @@ The orchestrator uses wakeup flags and `planner_pending` / `diagnostics_pending`\n ```\n Role emits message{to=Planner}\n   -> persist_inbound_message() writes last_message_to_planner.json + wakeup_planner.flag\n-  -> dispatch_state.planner_pending = true\n+  -> writer.apply(ControlEvent::PlannerPendingSet { pending: true })   [logged to tlog]\n   -> next orchestration loop iteration: apply_wake_flags() schedules planner\n   -> planner prompt injects inbound message via inject_inbound_message()\n ```\n@@ -368,9 +407,9 @@ If `cycle_progress = true` (work was dispatched) but all five hashes are unchang\n - The stall counter resets and the orchestrator enters the normal idle path.\n - Resuming requires a manual `wakeup_*.flag` write or process restart.\n \n-The stall counter is **not** incremented when executor turns are in flight (`submitted_turns`, `executor_submit_inflight`, or any `lane_submit_in_flight` non-empty). In-flight executor work legitimately produces no file change until the browser tab returns a result; counting those cycles as stalls would be a false positive.\n+The stall counter is **not** incremented when executor turns are in flight (`rt.submitted_turns`, `rt.executor_submit_inflight`, or any `writer.state().lane_submit_in_flight` value non-empty). In-flight executor work legitimately produces no file change until the browser tab returns a result; counting those cycles as stalls would be a false positive.\n \n-Implementation: `cycle_state_hash`, `write_livelock_report` in `src/app.rs`; constant `STALL_CYCLE_THRESHOLD = 5`.\n+Implementation: `cycle_state_hash`, `write_livelock_report` in `src/app.rs`; constant `STALL_CYCLE_THRESHOLD = 5`. Livelock detection reads inflight state from `RuntimeState` (`rt`) and serializable state from `writer.state()`.\n \n **Diagnostics report schema note:** The canonical `DiagnosticsReport` shape (defined in `src/reports.rs`) contains `status`, `inputs_scanned`, `ranked_failures`, and `planner_handoff`. The runtime reconciliation function (`reconcile_diagnostics_report` in `src/prompt_inputs.rs`) uses a typed round-trip through `DiagnosticsReport` so no unrecognised fields can be introduced — extra fields cannot survive re-serialisation of the struct.\n \n@@ -531,8 +570,9 @@ In self-modification mode only:\n \n **I13 — No permission escalation:** Executor must not patch `src/tools.rs::patch_scope_error` or any other scope-guard logic in a way that expands role permissions beyond SPEC.md §4. Any such patch requires verifier sign-off with explicit SPEC.md §4 justification.\n \n-**I14 — Checkpoint compatibility:** Changes to `OrchestratorCheckpoint` fields must use `#[serde(default)]` for additions. Removing or renaming fields requires a version bump or checkpoint discard on load. The `workspace` field must always be populated on save and validated on load.\n-Checkpoint `phase` values include `planner`, `executor`, `verifier`, `diagnostics`, and `solo`.\n+**I14 — Checkpoint and tlog compatibility:** Changes to `OrchestratorCheckpoint` fields must use `#[serde(default)]` for additions. Removing or renaming fields requires a version bump or checkpoint discard on load. The `workspace` field must always be populated on save and validated on load. Checkpoint `phase` values include `planner`, `executor`, `verifier`, `diagnostics`, and `solo`.\n+\n+Changes to `SystemState` fields follow the same rule: additions must use `#[serde(default)]`. The tlog (`AgentStateDir/tlog.ndjson`) is append-only and may contain entries from prior `SystemState` schemas; readers must tolerate unknown `ControlEvent` variants gracefully. Changes to `ControlEvent` variants are additive only — existing variants must not be renamed or removed while a tlog from that schema may be in service.\n \n ### 9.4 Safety Properties (Why It's Safe)\n - **No mid-run corruption:** The running orchestrator binary is already loaded into memory. Patching `src/` files does not affect the current process — changes take effect only on the next `cargo build` + process restart.\ndiff --git a/agent_state/last_planner_blocker_evidence.txt b/agent_state/last_planner_blocker_evidence.txt\nindex e1c672e..2102420 100644\n--- a/agent_state/last_planner_blocker_evidence.txt\n+++ b/agent_state/last_planner_blocker_evidence.txt\n@@ -1 +1 @@\n-auto-filled blocker evidence\n\\ No newline at end of file\n+The requested work requires authoritative mutation of PLAN.json via `plan` plus issue/objective bookkeeping updates, but no canon runtime executor is available here to apply those changes truthfully.\n\\ No newline at end of file\n"}},"seq":37,"ts_ms":1776123463159}
+{"event":{"class":"control","event":{"kind":"last_plan_text_set","text":"{\n  \"dag\": {\n    \"edges\": []\n  },\n  \"ready_window\": [],\n  \"status\": \"in_progress\",\n  \"tasks\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"enforce_promoted_invariant_inv_006454ec\",\n      \"issue_refs\": [\n        \"inv_gate_unenforced_inv_006454ec\"\n      ],\n      \"objective_id\": \"obj_39_close_promoted_invariant_enforcement_backlog\",\n      \"priority\": 1,\n      \"status\": \"done\",\n      \"steps\": [\n        \"Use agent_state/enforced_invariants.json: INV-006454ec requires actor_kind=verifier and error_class=verification_failed.\",\n        \"Inspect src/app.rs in dispatch_executor_submits route/executor gate region (~lines 1125-1290).\",\n        \"Add invariant-state injection: when verifier verification_failed recent count >= threshold, insert actor_kind=verifier and error_class=verification_failed into state before evaluate_invariant_gate.\",\n        \"Ensure this feeds into existing evaluate_invariant_gate(\\\"route\\\" or \\\"executor\\\") without breaking existing ordering.\",\n        \"Preserve all existing invariant semantics and blocking behavior.\",\n        \"Run cargo build --workspace.\",\n        \"Run cargo test --workspace.\"\n      ],\n      \"title\": \"Enforce promoted invariant INV-006454ec in runtime dispatch\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"reduce_dispatch_executor_submits_complexity_phase1\",\n      \"issue_refs\": [\n        \"auto_branch_reduce_canon_mini_agent_0f2928230a1e73d0\",\n        \"auto_inter_complexity_canon_mini_agent_1bc1996b7bc9ac2\"\n      ],\n      \"objective_id\": \"obj_reduce_inter_function_complexity_hotspots\",\n      \"priority\": 2,\n      \"status\": \"done\",\n      \"steps\": [\n        \"Inspect src/app.rs:1100-1300 and identify largest branching clusters.\",\n        \"Extract one branch cluster into a helper function preserving behavior.\",\n        \"Ensure no change to invariant gate ordering or dispatch semantics.\",\n        \"Run cargo build --workspace.\",\n        \"Run cargo test --workspace.\"\n      ],\n      \"title\": \"Reduce branch complexity in dispatch_executor_submits (phase 1 extraction)\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"fix_route_gate_invalid_route_livelock_cluster\",\n      \"issue_refs\": [\n        \"route_gate_invalid_route_livelock_cluster\"\n      ],\n      \"objective_id\": \"obj_39a_route_gate_promoted_invariant_progress\",\n      \"priority\": 1,\n      \"status\": \"done\",\n      \"steps\": [\n        \"Inspect src/app.rs around lines 1125-1280 and identify the exact route-gate / invalid_route path producing recurrent churn.\",\n        \"Patch the narrowest routing or precondition path so executor dispatch no longer loops on the same invalid_route blocker when inputs are otherwise recoverable.\",\n        \"Preserve invariant-gate semantics and avoid regressing existing promoted invariant enforcement behavior.\",\n        \"Run cargo build --workspace.\",\n        \"Run cargo test --workspace.\"\n      ],\n      \"title\": \"Fix route-gate invalid_route livelock before executor dispatch\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"reopen_route_gate_invalid_route_livelock_cluster_phase2\",\n      \"issue_refs\": [\n        \"route_gate_invalid_route_livelock_cluster\"\n      ],\n      \"objective_id\": \"obj_39a_route_gate_promoted_invariant_progress\",\n      \"priority\": 1,\n      \"status\": \"blocked\",\n      \"steps\": [\n        \"Inspect `src/app.rs` around `evaluate_executor_route_gates` and the `dispatch_executor_submits` call site to identify the remaining invalid_route churn path under the helper-based layout.\",\n        \"Inspect fresh blocker evidence in `agent_state/blockers.json` and recent action-log evidence in `agent_state/default/actions.jsonl` to confirm the exact invalid_route trigger still dominating current cycles.\",\n        \"Patch the narrowest remaining route-gate / precondition path so repeated recoverable `invalid_route` churn no longer hard-loops planner/executor dispatch.\",\n        \"Preserve promoted invariant evaluation order, blocker recording, and all existing gate semantics outside the repaired path.\",\n        \"Run `cargo build --workspace`.\",\n        \"Run `cargo test --workspace`.\"\n      ],\n      \"title\": \"Reopen route-gate invalid_route livelock repair against helper-based gate path\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"enforce_promoted_invariant_inv_a650f28b\",\n      \"issue_refs\": [\n        \"inv_gate_unenforced_inv_a650f28b\"\n      ],\n      \"objective_id\": \"obj_39_close_promoted_invariant_enforcement_backlog\",\n      \"priority\": 1,\n      \"status\": \"done\",\n      \"steps\": [\n        \"Inspect `src/app.rs` around `evaluate_executor_route_gates` and the current helper-based route-gate state assembly referenced by `inv_gate_unenforced_inv_a650f28b`.\",\n        \"Inspect `agent_state/enforced_invariants.json` and `src/invariants.rs` for the exact predicate and required state tuple for INV-a650f28b.\",\n        \"Patch the narrowest helper-based invariant-state injection or gate wiring so INV-a650f28b is enforced without changing unrelated route/executor invariant ordering.\",\n        \"Preserve blocker recording, planner wake behavior, and existing gate semantics outside the repaired predicate path.\",\n        \"Run `cargo build --workspace`.\",\n        \"Run `cargo test --workspace`.\"\n      ],\n      \"title\": \"Enforce promoted invariant INV-a650f28b in helper-based route gating\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"T1_route_gate_livelock_recovery_plan\",\n      \"priority\": 1,\n      \"status\": \"done\",\n      \"steps\": [\n        \"Inspect src/app.rs route-gate evaluation and dispatch paths using symbol_window.\",\n        \"Identify the exact condition causing repeated invalid_route without state progression.\",\n        \"Correlate findings with runtime logs in agent_state if available.\",\n        \"Design a minimal guard or state transition to prevent identical re-entry into invalid_route path.\",\n        \"Verify invariant enforcement ordering and ensure no regression in existing gate semantics.\"\n      ],\n      \"title\": \"Recover from route-gate invalid_route livelock and enforce remaining invariants\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"T_reduce_planner_prompt_overflow_top_n_compaction\",\n      \"issue_refs\": [\n        \"prompt_overflow_planner_followup_pending_reverification\"\n      ],\n      \"objective_id\": \"obj_14_derive_hardcoded_metadata\",\n      \"priority\": 2,\n      \"status\": \"done\",\n      \"steps\": [\n        \"Regression-test linkage: if any source change becomes necessary, add or update a focused regression test or probe that exercises the authoritative planner prompt measurement path and asserts planner prompt bytes stay at or below `PROMPT_OVERFLOW_BYTES = 80000` before this task is marked done again.\",\n        \"Read `agent_state/canon-mini-agent-logs.log` as the primary same-cycle planner prompt measurement artifact.\",\n        \"Confirm the planner log is current-cycle fresh before trusting values.\",\n        \"Parse the most recent fresh `[planner] step=<n> prompt_bytes=<m>` entries and compare each `<m>` against `PROMPT_OVERFLOW_BYTES = 80000`.\",\n        \"If fresh current-cycle planner entries are all `<= 80000`, capture the concrete log evidence and stop without source changes.\",\n        \"Only if a fresh current-cycle planner entry exceeds `80000`, continue the narrowest planner-context compaction path while preserving high-priority objectives and open-issue context.\",\n        \"Run `cargo build --workspace` after any code change.\",\n        \"Run `cargo test --workspace` after any code change.\"\n      ],\n      \"title\": \"Reduce planner prompt injection size below the overflow threshold\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"enforce_promoted_invariant_inv_c2b90a1d\",\n      \"issue_refs\": [\n        \"inv_gate_unenforced_inv_c2b90a1d\"\n      ],\n      \"objective_id\": \"obj_39_close_promoted_invariant_enforcement_backlog\",\n      \"priority\": 1,\n      \"status\": \"done\",\n      \"steps\": [\n        \"Inspect `agent_state/enforced_invariants.json` for the exact predicate and required state tuple for `INV-c2b90a1d` (`actor_kind=solo`, `error_class=verification_failed`).\",\n        \"Inspect `src/app.rs` route-gate state assembly and locate the current incorrect `actor_kind=verifier` wiring for `verification_failed`.\",\n        \"Patch the narrowest route-gate state injection so the `verification_failed` path feeds `actor_kind=solo` with `error_class=verification_failed` before invariant evaluation.\",\n        \"Preserve all existing route/executor gate ordering and other invariant-state injections.\",\n        \"Add or update a focused regression test that exercises the `solo` + `verification_failed` predicate path for `INV-c2b90a1d`.\",\n        \"Run `cargo build --workspace`.\",\n        \"Run `cargo test --workspace`.\"\n      ],\n      \"title\": \"Enforce promoted invariant INV-c2b90a1d in runtime dispatch\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"enforce_promoted_invariant_inv_77eff017\",\n      \"issue_refs\": [\n        \"inv_gate_unenforced_inv_77eff017\"\n      ],\n      \"objective_id\": \"obj_39_close_promoted_invariant_enforcement_backlog\",\n      \"priority\": 1,\n      \"status\": \"done\",\n      \"steps\": [\n        \"Inspect `agent_state/enforced_invariants.json` for the exact predicate, support evidence, and required state tuple for `INV-77eff017`.\",\n        \"Inspect `src/app.rs` around lines `1011-1050` to find the narrowest missing invariant-state injection or gate wiring for `INV-77eff017`.\",\n        \"Patch only the missing invariant-state injection or gate wiring needed for `INV-77eff017`, preserving existing route/executor ordering and blocker semantics.\",\n        \"Add or update a focused regression test that exercises the `INV-77eff017` predicate path so the issue cannot silently reopen.\",\n        \"Run `cargo build --workspace`.\",\n        \"Run `cargo test --workspace`.\"\n      ],\n      \"title\": \"Enforce promoted invariant INV-77eff017 in runtime dispatch\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"version\": 2\n}"}},"seq":38,"ts_ms":1776123620855}
